  .row
    .columns.small-12.large-8.group
      h3.headline-3 Platform Technical Capabilities
      markdown:
        Datica supports two primary methods of getting your software running on the Platform: [Buildpacks](#) with `git push`, and [Container Services](#) with `datica deploy`. Between these two methods, Datica can support almost any technology imaginable on the application layer. When it comes to services with volumes, we're a bit more prescriptive, given how automatic backups and disaster recovery works.
        {:.lead}
  .row.align-center
    .columns.small-12.medium-4.large-4
      = inline_svg("icon-code", class: "icon-size--small svg-color--gray-3")
      h5.headline-5 Common Languages
      p Datica supports hundreds of languages and frameworks. Here are a few popular ones:
      ul.no-bullet.multicol-2.group
        li Ruby
        li Node.js
        li Clojure
        li Python
        li Java
        li Gradle
        li Grails 3.x
        li Scala
        li Play 2.x
        li PHP
        li Go
    .columns.small-12.medium-4.large-2
      = inline_svg("icon-database-hotswap", class: "icon-size--small svg-color--gray-3")
      h5.headline-5 Database Support
      ul.no-bullet.group
        li Percona/MySQL
        li PostgreSQL
        li MongoDB
      = inline_svg("icon-network", class: "icon-size--small svg-color--gray-3")
      h5.headline-5 Other Services
      ul.no-bullet.group
        li Redis
        li Memcached
        li RabbitMQ
    .columns.small-12.medium-4.large-6
      = inline_svg("icon-windows", class: "icon-size--small svg-color--gray-3")
      h5.headline-5 Windows architecture support
      ul.no-bullet.group
        li Windows VMs on dedicated accounts
        li Microsoft SQL Server
      .callout.drop-light
        = inline_svg("icon-docker", class: "icon-size--large float-right svg-color--gray-3")
